        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 24 at 5:38PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 538 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 6 miles southeast of New Salem to 8 miles
northwest of Bedford to 6 miles northwest of Kolola Springs. Movement
was east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Hamilton, Vernon, Sulligent, Guin, Detroit, Beaverton, Blooming
Grove, Lamar County Airport, Crews, Bedford, Crossville, Henson
Springs, Lamar County Public Lake, Rankin Fite Airport, Star, Pine
Springs, Byrd, Marion County Public Lake, Hightogy, and Pikeville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
